<subSubSection id="6F72A2E77640E24C58A93C8F27CCBAA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="E7190464E7580C61523186DADF8EC309" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="D21C267685A7BC442321C2E4924D5F16" LSID="ED9272AA-2C00-5A10-A8A2-63C10058F5B8" authority="Andersson, 1960" authorityName="Andersson" authorityYear="1960" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae " genus="Pectenoniscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pectenoniscus" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pectenoniscus Andersson, 1960</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F6257A2DFEEC49953DE11AD87A491F38" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="type species">
<paragraph id="4FF8E34968153687AD4945DB6E93CC7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Type species.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="459625DE5F0C709C28DE0AEF52341B22" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
<taxonomicName id="EC858331708274FE2333116A8057793F" authorityName="Andersson" authorityYear="1960" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae " genus="Pectenoniscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pectenoniscus angulatus" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis id="F6C7F9BC79AA175576747EBFEC9DC885" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Pectenoniscus angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Andersson, 1960 by monotypy (see 
<bibRefCitation id="861AD9CBC707330D21CC67C181964BE8" author="Schmidt, C" journalOrPublisher="Steenstrupia" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 118" refId="B47" refString="Schmidt, C, Leistikow, A, 2004. Catalogue of genera of the terrestrial Isopoda (Crustacea: Isopoda: Oniscidea). Steenstrupia 28: 1 - 118" title="Catalogue of genera of the terrestrial Isopoda (Crustacea: Isopoda: Oniscidea)." volume="28" year="2004">Schmidt and Leistikow 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F70532E44BFEE786028DBF4A533C4E97" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DB28271D8DA68E88F829CDA11DF28EEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25B57AE9A6678FFCD785FDC64F74DFAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
After 
<bibRefCitation id="384956373161659979276805C56EAE12" author="Andersson, A" journalOrPublisher="Arkiv foer Zoologi" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="537 - 570" refId="B2" refString="Andersson, A, 1960. South American terrestrial isopods in the collection of the Swedish State Museum of Natural History. Arkiv foer Zoologi 12: 537 - 570" title="South American terrestrial isopods in the collection of the Swedish State Museum of Natural History." volume="12" year="1960">Andersson (1960)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9ACF3CCEE6195581522F4A537127E9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4564.2.6" author="Campos-Filho, IS" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="422 - 448" refId="B16" refString="Campos-Filho, IS, Fernandes, CS, Cardoso, GM, Bichuette, ME, Aguiar, JO, Taiti, S, 2019. Two new species and new records of terrestrial isopods (Crustacea, Isopoda, Oniscidea) from Brazilian caves. Zootaxa 4564 (2): 422 - 448, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4564.2.6" title="Two new species and new records of terrestrial isopods (Crustacea, Isopoda, Oniscidea) from Brazilian caves." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4564.2.6" volume="4564" year="2019">Campos-Filho et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
. Animals of reduced size, ≤ 3.5 mm. Body unpigmented and eyes absent. Body slender with lateral sides almost parallel. Dorsal surface of cephalon and pereon bearing small transverse tubercles, conferring granulated appearance, pleon smooth or slightly tuberculate. Cephalon with 4-6 rows of tubercles, gradually reducing in number from posterior to distal portion, pereonite 1 with two or three rows of tubercles, pereonites 2-7 with two rows of tubercles. Dorsal scale-setae triangular. Cephalon with antennary lobes and suprantennal line. Pleonites 3-5 epimera not developed (only developed in 
<taxonomicName id="B5A7FF21EEEECAD9C04E01D54338E9CB" genus="P." lsidName="P. angulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis id="0AB105FF32C0CCDD3EFEFD63639EA67F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Telson triangular with lateral sides concave and rounded apex. Antennula of three articles, distal article with aesthetascs arranged in one longitudinal row. Antennal flagellum of 3-5 articles. Mandibles with strong molar process, left mandible with two penicils, right mandible with one penicil (sometimes one penicil on molar process). Maxillula inner endite with three penicils, proximal one longest; outer endite composed of eight or nine teeth plus slender stalks. Maxilla of two lobes covered with thick and fine setae, inner lobe wider. Maxilliped basis with lateral sides almost parallel, endite rectangular bearing one stout penicil. Uropod protopod subquadrangular, exopod longer than endopod, protopod and exopod sometimes bearing glandular pores, endopod inserted proximally. Male pleopod 1 endopod of two articles, distal article flagelliform. Male pleopod 2 endopod consisting of two articles, distal portion stout bearing complex apparatus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9664B72C1B87269ECF51AF4B8A450207" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="2C52A3EBB88283C0025F2FD0EAF0BA95" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA7CC93B591471EA243867263050D511" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="D76356115418AFF0CC191AB627AB40D1" authorityName="Andersson" authorityYear="1960" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae " genus="Pectenoniscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pectenoniscus" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C806084B6E0A97A8D8A9EC49710615D5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Pectenoniscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was created by 
<bibRefCitation id="0E81EBC726CA19A7DD02AF21CAAE58B4" author="Andersson, A" journalOrPublisher="Arkiv foer Zoologi" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="537 - 570" refId="B2" refString="Andersson, A, 1960. South American terrestrial isopods in the collection of the Swedish State Museum of Natural History. Arkiv foer Zoologi 12: 537 - 570" title="South American terrestrial isopods in the collection of the Swedish State Museum of Natural History." volume="12" year="1960">Andersson (1960)</bibRefCitation>
to allocate the new species 
<taxonomicName id="E55EE361256FDA4270753208CACD8DCC" genus="P." lsidName="P. angulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis id="1C256A221427F041B213E43B446A1A61" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken id="8A1BDED2850F639986D2754BE158083A" originalValue="Itá">Ita</normalizedToken>
, Nova 
<normalizedToken id="98B480E4352647965047DFDBB33A070A" originalValue="Teutônia">Teutonia</normalizedToken>
, state of Santa Catarina, Brazil. The author defined the genus by having the cephalon of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="4A91828DAAED1C11C9460542200AC172" authorityName="Brandt" authorityYear="1833" class="Malacostraca" family="Trichoniscidae" genus="Trichoniscus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trichoniscus" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8F5B5442B5012A4E084C37D7D5FB290D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Trichoniscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-type&quot;, dorsal surface of the cephalon and pereon with rounded tubercles, pleonites epimera large, left mandible with two penicils near lacinia mobilis, right mandible with one penicil near lacinia mobilis plus one in the molar process, maxillula outer endite composed of nine teeth and two slender stalks, inner endite of three penicils and proximal one longer than distal ones, genital papilla pear-shaped with tubelike termination, male pleopod 1 of &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="95577A005BAEF7CAC9E6522AE9BF1BED" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1853" class="Malacostraca" family="Styloniscidae" genus="Styloniscus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Styloniscus" order="Isopoda" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="909D19879E5DEFB059A6A30E87AAF127" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">Styloniscus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-type&quot;, male pleopod 2 endopod with distal portion broad and bearing a comb-like formation, and male pleopod 5 exopods with a dorsal lobe to fit the pleopod 2 endopod. 
<bibRefCitation id="BA0755B46AAE91E9A334C9142128F554" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4564.2.6" author="Campos-Filho, IS" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="422 - 448" refId="B16" refString="Campos-Filho, IS, Fernandes, CS, Cardoso, GM, Bichuette, ME, Aguiar, JO, Taiti, S, 2019. Two new species and new records of terrestrial isopods (Crustacea, Isopoda, Oniscidea) from Brazilian caves. Zootaxa 4564 (2): 422 - 448, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4564.2.6" title="Two new species and new records of terrestrial isopods (Crustacea, Isopoda, Oniscidea) from Brazilian caves." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4564.2.6" volume="4564" year="2019">Campos-Filho et al. (2019)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="284EF55EFFA147F61D891F44B1314B13" genus="P." lsidName="P. liliae" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="liliae">
<emphasis id="5FAC9BCD0AC1E30736E1B07E0DAA7AB6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. liliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Campos-Filho, Bichuette &amp; Taiti, 2019 from Caverna Chico Pernambuco, Coribe, Serra do Ramalho karst area, state of Bahia, and added some characters in the diagnosis of the genus. Recently, 
<bibRefCitation id="8C4F8CF4A46B62D0F6F701DD0843CCBF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1590/2358-2936e2020039" author="Cardoso, GM" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" refId="B20" refString="Cardoso, GM, Bastos-Pereira, R, Souza, LA, Ferreira, RL, 2020b. New cave species of Pectenoniscus Andersson, 1960 (Isopoda: Oniscidea: Styloniscidae) and an identification key for the genus. Nauplius 28: e2020039. https://doi.org/10.1590/2358-2936e2020039" title="New cave species of Pectenoniscus Andersson, 1960 (Isopoda: Oniscidea: Styloniscidae) and an identification key for the genus. Nauplius 28: e 2020039." url="https://doi.org/10.1590/2358-2936e2020039" year="2020 b">Cardoso et al. (2020b)</bibRefCitation>
described six new species from karst areas of the states of Bahia and Minas Gerais, increasing the knowledge on the diversity of the genus, that now comprises eight species, i.e., 
<taxonomicName id="F13ADCC78A801A075F4BB465E450E793" genus="P." lsidName="P. angulatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="angulatus">
<emphasis id="4EB65338A1F93BDF495169883328072C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. angulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BF697AD4AC57A74865F79944531DD31C" genus="P." lsidName="P. carinhanhensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" rank="species" species="carinhanhensis">
<emphasis id="05FEA07AD7C983E24F2547FFF0C40D26" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">P. carinhanhensis</emphasis>
